<subSubSection id="C3496558FFBCFFB6FF7FB85CFC18F83D" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFBCFFB6FF7FB85CFEB2F875" blockId="7.[151,1437,1585,2008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">
Type data: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFBCFFB6FEF2B85CFE07F995" author="Friese, H." box="[330,495,1622,1648]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref6002" refString="Friese, H. (1899 a) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese (1899a)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on two females from 
<collectingCountry id="F3447643FFBCFFB6FBFBB85CFB6FF995" box="[1091,1159,1622,1648]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(“ 
<collectingRegion id="4997F831FFBCFFB6FB1CB85CFB34F995" box="[1188,1244,1622,1648]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Para</collectingRegion>
” and “Brasilia”) housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBCFFB6FEB6B870FEBFF971" box="[270,343,1658,1684]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">NMW</collectionCode>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFBCFFB6FEDBB870FDAFF971" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[355,583,1658,1684]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref6580" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBCFFB6FE00B871FE04F971" box="[440,492,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the type series was housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBCFFB6FBE7B870FB76F971" box="[1119,1182,1658,1684]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
, but no primary types were found in either of those institutions. In the 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBCFFB6FD16B894FCECF95D" box="[686,772,1694,1720]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">HNHM</collectionCode>
I found two females, one labeled “Brasilia” and “669 236”, and another one with similar labels, but also containing an original Friese identification label. This latter specimen is here designated 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBCFFB6FEC8B8ECFE32F8E5" box="[368,474,1766,1792]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The female has the following data label: Brasilia [printed]\ [light greenish square] 74. [handwritten]\ [black-rimmed] 669. 235 [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBCFFB6FC80B900FC3BF8C1" authority="Vivallo, 2019" authorityName="Vivallo" authorityYear="2019" box="[824,979,1802,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBCFFB6FC80B900FC3BF8C1" box="[824,979,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Centris klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21457BAFFBCFFB6FC63B900FBF0F8C1" box="[987,1048,1802,1828]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<specimenCount id="9D55FD5AFFBCFFB6FB99B900FBDEF8C1" box="[1057,1078,1802,1828]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
[handwritten] det. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFBCFFB6FAA8B900FA74F8C1" author="Friese, H." box="[1296,1436,1802,1828]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" pagination="427 - 431" refId="ref5980" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Trigona - Arten Australiens. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 21, 427 - 431." type="journal article" year="1898">Friese, 1898</bibRefCitation>
[printed].According to the accession book at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBCFFB6FD34B924FD0AF8AD" box="[652,738,1838,1864]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">HNHM</collectionCode>
these specimens were obtained as exchange materials and gifts by Mocsáry during his trip to 
<collectingCountry id="F3447643FFBCFFB6FE5CB958FDA4F889" box="[484,588,1874,1900]" name="Germany" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Germany</collectingCountry>
in 1883. The depository and the current condition of the 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBCFFB6FB70B958FAB7F889" box="[1224,1375,1874,1900]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">paralectotype</typeStatus>
from Pará is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFBCFFB6FF7FB990FE5DF851" blockId="7.[151,1437,1585,2008]" box="[199,437,1946,1972]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">
<materialsCitation id="3B3B3C8EFFBCFFB6FF7FB990FE59F851" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2284429102" box="[199,433,1946,1972]" country="Brazil" location="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBCFFB6FF7FB990FF17F851" box="[199,255,1946,1972]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Type</typeStatus>
locality: 
<collectingCountry id="F3447643FFBCFFB6FED1B990FE59F851" box="[361,433,1946,1972]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">Brazil</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFBCFFB6FF7FB9B4FC18F83D" blockId="7.[151,1437,1585,2008]" box="[199,1008,1982,2008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">
Comment: This species was correctly interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFBCFFB6FCADB9B4FC18F83D" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[789,1008,1982,2008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="541" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref6580" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBCFFB6FCDEB9B5FC70F83D" box="[870,920,1982,2008]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="541">et al</emphasis>
